result.execSummary:
The defendant Georgiana Joni Carson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Georgiana Joni Carson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Georgiana Joni Carson was found guilty of Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Georgiana Joni Carson was found guilty of Possess Drug Paraphernalia [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
10:05 AM Prosecuting attorney James Jay Rennicke Esq in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Georgiana Joni Carson in court.  Attorney Eugene D Harrington in court for Georgiana Joni Carson. Case is on for Sentencing Hearing.  Parties acknowledge receipt of PSI, DA proposes no corrections or modifications.  Atty Harrington updates the court- def now believes there is a conflict between defendant and atty, def wants another opinion/representation.  Court questions defendant.  Atty Harrington wishes to supplement the PSI with medical records; otherwise no corrections or modifications to the PSI.  Court will not adjourn.  State argues for 1 year county jail, w/court costs.  Atty Harrington objects during sentencing argument of the State; court responds.  Atty Harrington provides documentation to the Court.  Defense attorney argues for 1-2 yrs probation.  Defendant makes a statement.  
Court orders: 
Ct 2- Possession of THC (2nd)- 1.5 yrs probation, withheld; $518 court costs
Ct 3- Possession of drug paraphernalia- 1 day jail, 1 day jail credit, $200 DNA surcharge.
Conditions of probation:
Complete outpatient treatment and services.  No use/possession firearms- life.  No use or possession of any illegal drugs, paraphernalia, or controlled substances without a valid prescription. The defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety. Mental health evaluation and follow through.  No voting until civil rights restored.  Reg testing- if def tests positive for meth, must serve 30 days conditional jail for each positive test for methamphetamine- no good time, no Huber.  No contact with R.J. or D.C. or anyone on current supervision for any drug related offense- unless approved by Agent, except for K.B. (def's sister).
Defendant must provide DNA to the BCSD prior to leaving the building.  Def to pay $25/month to Clerk of Courts.
Appeal rights provided.
Sentencing hearing on July 11, 2022 at 10:00 am.

03:29 PM Defendant, Georgiana Joni Carson, appeared with Attorney Eugene D Harrington.  Attorney James Rennicke appeared for the State.  Court reviews file, did WOPH on 3/7/22 and no Information filed.  Parties to waive time limits to Info.  Case is on for Plea/Sentencing Hearing.  Discussion, Court confirms WOPH with def, def understands and waives her rights with regard to the preliminary hearing KIV.  Agreement is recited by Attorney Harrington, def intends to plead to Counts 2 and 3; PSI, parties free to argue.  Court asks def if they understand the agreement.  Def does.  Court reviews Defs constitutional rights.  Def understands that def is waiving those rights by entering into agreement today.  Court asks Def if they understand Court is not bound by agreement, and could order maximum penalties.  Def understands.  Court asks for pleas.  Def enters a plea of Guilty to Counts 2 and 3.  Court finds def is making pleas knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily.  Court finds a factual basis to accept the pleas.  Court finds defendant guilty of Counts 2 and 3 and orders a JOC; Counts 1 and 4 are DRI; Count 5 is dismissed outright.  Court orders PSI, long form, agent does not need to be present, but should be available by phone- if needed- for sentencing hearing.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for July 11, 2022 at 10:00 am.
